:R-HSA-1299361  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0071805 ;
        rdfs:comment        "TWIK related alkaline pH activated K+ channels are activated by increase in the extracellular pH. TALK1 and TALK 2 are members of the TALK subfamily and are both are activated by rise in extracellular pH. TALK 2 is expressed in proximal tubule cells and collecting duct cells. TASK 2 is involved in the resorption of bicarbonate." ;
        rdfs:label          "TWIK-related alkaline pH activated K+ channel (TALK)" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Mahajan, SS, 2011-05-22" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Mahajan, SS, 2011-05-23" , "Reviewed: Jassal, Bijay, 2010-09-23" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
